Introduction
------------

This is the binary component of the GrADS distribution.  You'll
need the version 1.6+ data files (geography, fonts and symbols)
to run this version.  See the GrADS-VVV/README above for more information.


Contents of GrADS-VVV/bin/
--------------------------

This are the standard executables that come with the binary distribution:

GrADS:

gradsnc		-    Full featured GrADS using the UNIDATA netCDF libraries
gradshdf	-    Full featured GrADS using the NCSA netCDF/HDF libraries 
gradsc		-    Classic GrADS - no LATS, GUI, SDF or netcdf (readline only)
grads		-    link to gradshdf

GrADS Utilities:

gxps		-	convert grads meta graphics to postscript level 1 
gxtran		-	display grads meta graphics
gribmap		-	GRIB mapping utility
gribscan	-	GRIB scanning utility
stnmap		-	station data mapper

Contributed Utilities:

gxeps		-    grads meta graphics to EPS utility
gxgif		-    grads meta graphics to GIF utility
wgrib		-    GRIB lister/processor from NCEP (see wesley.wwb.noaa.gov)


New Features of GrADS 1.7:

LATS (Mike Fiorino):
--------------------

Interface to the Library for AMIP data Transmission Standards
(LATS) allowing GrADS to output GRIB and/or netCDF (unidata (gradsnc) or
HDF SDF (grasdhdf)

http://www-pcmdi.llnl.gov/software/lats


SDF/XDF (Don Hooper):
---------------------

Open netCDF/HDF-SDF COARDS compliant files

http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~hoop/grads3.html


External scriptable GUI (Arlindo da Silva):
-------------------------------------------

Add a GUI to GrADS

ftp://niteroi.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/win32/grads/doc/gagui_intro.html



Hints
-----

Running GrADS or the GrADS the utilities with the "-help" command line
option will list command line options.

Running the Contributed Utilities with NO command line options
will list the options.


